title: Junior High Football: Streaks 7th graders get by Mid-County
text: Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:19 PM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:19 PM GALESBURG â€” The Galesburg Junior High seventh grade football team defeated Mid-County 24-14 on Saturday. The Streaks (8-1) were led by Kyleb Meadows with 93 yards rushing and one touchdown. Alex Sword had 50 yards rushing and a TD and Xavier Coleman also scored a TD and recovered a fumble for Galesburg. Kyron Leath had five tackles followed by Alejandro Morales with four and Damonte Jenkins and Cameron Kelly each finished with three tackles with Jenkins also picking off a Mid-County pass.
